SKILL|yvon-development|"YVON 2.0 / YVON-OS Next.js dashboard development ‚Äî Hermes agent integration, venture rotation, analytics architecture, LifeOS-inspired UI patterns, and the patterns that connect the 13-agent system to the web UI. Covers both repos: OfficialNovizio/YVON2.0 and OfficialNovizio/YVON-OS."
STEP|1|User mentions YVON, Novizio, Hourbour, YVON OS, or YVON-OS
STEP|2|Working in `/root/yvon/` or `/root/yvon-os/` directories
STEP|3|Task touches `app/screens/`, `app/api/`, `lib/`, or agent integration
STEP|4|User asks about dashboard, analytics, CEO command, War Room, Decision Queue, or any YVON screen
STEP|5|**32 LifeOS-style pages**: Decision Queue, Task Board, Advisory Council, Agents, Org Chart, Content Pipeline, Social Approvals, Scheduler, Newsletter, Brain & Wiki, Asset Lab, Software Pipeline, Email
STEP|6|**Sidebar navigation**: Grouped sections (Command Center, Long-form, Shorts, Posts, Knowledge, Build, Revenue, System) with count badges
STEP|7|**Venture-only theming**: 2 real ventures only ‚Äî `novizio` crimson #E94560, `hourbour` ocean #3B82F6. No visual workspaces (vibe/canela/valhalla/bydesign were removed). Venture accents in `app/globals
STEP|8|**Settings page**: Expandable cards layout (NOT tabs). Venture Profile + Socials are editable, System sections are read-only. User explicitly rejected tabs ‚Äî use click-to-expand cards.
STEP|9|**Design system**: Dark obsidian theme with Material Design 3 colors, glass cards, kanban components, venture-accented nav links
STEP|10|**All YVON 2.0 backend**: Same Supabase, API routes, lib modules, agents, migrations, CI/CD
STEP|11|Loading order for YVON-OS sessions:**
STEP|12|Read `yvon-os/README.md` and `yvon-os/docs/briefs/00-Page-Inventory.md` for the page map
STEP|13|Read the specific page briefing from `docs/briefs/` for the task at hand
STEP|14|Cross-reference with YVON 2.0 docs at `docs/` for venture context, agent memories, design specs
STEP|15|Migration pattern: `references/yvon-os-migration.md`** ‚Äî 11-phase checklist for merging YVON 2.0 backend into YVON-OS.
STEP|16|Component porting: `references/component-porting-pattern.md`** ‚Äî adapting YVON 2.0 components to YVON-OS design system (glass tokens ‚Üí Tailwind + CSS vars, venture context ‚Üí WorkspaceContext).
STEP|17|Feature placement: `references/feature-placement-map.md`** ‚Äî where each YVON 2.0 feature goes in YVON-OS, with priority order.
STEP|18|Data fetching: `references/useLiveData-hook.md`** ‚Äî shared `useLiveData` hook for unified loading/error/mock states across all wired pages.
STEP|19|Repo swap: `references/repo-swap-pattern.md`** ‚Äî swapping YVON-OS into YVON2.0 repo with backup branch, .env.local preservation, and Vercel auto-deploy trigger.
STEP|20|Phase 3 wiring: `references/phase-3-wiring-pattern.md`** ‚Äî the API route ‚Üí useLiveData hook ‚Üí page component pattern used to wire mock pages to live Supabase data.
STEP|21|Phase 4 parallel wiring: `references/phase-4-parallel-wiring.md`** ‚Äî wiring 8+ pages in parallel via `delegate_task` sub-agents, with build-failure guard patterns.
STEP|22|LifeOS gap analysis** in `yvon-dashboard-overhaul` skill, `references/lifeos-gap-analysis.md`.
STEP|23|**Plan**: Write a plan document to `docs/plans/<feature>-plan.md`. The plan must cover: what files change, what API routes are needed, what data flows (Supabase tables), what UI changes. **One page pe
STEP|24|**Approve**: User reviews plan, requests changes, or gives the go-ahead. Wait for explicit approval. Do NOT start building until approved.
STEP|25|**Build**: Write all code. Create UI components, API routes, wire data. Run `npx tsc --noEmit` after every file. Keep commits atomic per feature. **Port components from YVON 2.0, don't redesign**. See
STEP|26|**Verify with technical team**: This is NOT optional. After writing code, use `delegate_task` to spawn:
STEP|27|**Push**: Commit with descriptive message, push to GitHub. Verify CI passes (lint ‚Üí typecheck ‚Üí build ‚Üí test ‚Üí deploy).
STEP|28|Deployment rule (MANDATORY):** NEVER run `vercel --prod` or `npx vercel` manually. Push to GitHub ONLY. Vercel deployments happen automatically via GitHub Actions CI (`amondnet/vercel-action@v25` in `
STEP|29|Pre-push checklist ‚Äî run ALL of these before `git push`:**
STEP|30|**Ask**: "Are you on the `master` branch? Not `backup/yvon2-legacy` or `legacy-v1`?"
STEP|31|**Check target repo**: `git remote -v` should point to `OfficialNovizio/YVON2.0` ‚Äî NOT `YVON-OS` (that repo no longer exists, returns 404)
STEP|32|**Fresh clone command**: `git clone https://github.com/OfficialNovizio/YVON2.0.git && cd YVON2.0 && git checkout master`
STEP|33|**Repo naming confusion**: The GitHub repo is named `YVON2.0` but contains YVON OS code. The old YVON 2.0 code lives in the `backup/yvon2-legacy` branch. There is no separate YVON-OS repo. The sidebar
STEP|34|Pitfall**: Don't assume the user's local clone is up to date. A stale clone on the wrong branch produces reports of "missing features" that are actually present in HEAD. Verify git state before modify
STEP|35|Common lint error patterns and fixes:** `references/lint-error-patterns.md` ‚Äî react/no-unescaped-entities, prefer-const, and how to fix them.
STEP|36|User preference**: The user explicitly said "don't rush take time, relax, i don't want errors" and "each phase need plan and approval." This means: thorough over fast, verified over assumed, plan-befo
STEP|37|How it works (`lib/WorkspaceContext.tsx`):**
STEP|38|Persistence**: Workspace key persists in `localStorage` (`yvon_active_workspace`). On mount, restores from localStorage AND syncs the venture cookie. Only `'novizio'` and `'hourbour'` are valid keys ‚Äî
STEP|39|CSS accents**: `app/globals.css` has `[data-workspace='novizio']` and `[data-workspace='hourbour']` blocks setting `--ws-accent`, `--ws-accent-soft`, and `--ws-glow`.
STEP|40|Pitfall**: The `WorkspaceKey` type is now `'novizio' \| 'hourbour'` ONLY. Do NOT add `'vibe'`, `'canela'`, `'valhalla'`, or `'bydesign'` back ‚Äî they were removed.
STEP|41|`/api/ventures` ‚Äî per-venture profile (editable form, saves via PATCH /api/ventures/[id])
STEP|42|`/api/ventures/[id]/socials` ‚Äî social media accounts per venture
STEP|43|`/api/dashboard` ‚Äî system health, AI provider balance, tokens, DB status
STEP|44|Sections (expandable cards, not tabs):**
STEP|45|Venture Profile ‚Äî editable form (name, slug, color, brand type, brand tier, status, tagline, description, website, repo, notion, year). Save writes to Supabase.
STEP|46|Social Media ‚Äî 10 platforms, add/remove per venture
STEP|47|Infrastructure ‚Äî read-only per-venture links
STEP|48|System status cards ‚Äî AI Provider, Database, API Keys, System Health, Security, Preferences (persistent localStorage toggles)
STEP|49|NO Switch Venture section in Settings** ‚Äî venture switching is ONLY in the TopBar pill.
STEP|50|**All AI calls go through `/api/` routes** ‚Äî never call external APIs from client components. Client fetches `/api/*`, the route handler makes the external call server-side.
STEP|51|**Venture context flows via cookie** ‚Äî `yvon_active_venture` cookie set by VentureSwitcher. All screens read it via `useVentureSlug()` hook from `@/lib/use-venture-slug`.
STEP|52|**Glassmorphic design system** ‚Äî three glass variants (G1 Clear Ice, G2 Azure Tint, G3 Deep Ink) defined in CSS. Duplicated inline across pages ‚Äî prefer extracting to `_glass-tokens.ts` in each screen
STEP|53|**Strict TypeScript + Next.js build** ‚Äî zero errors after every change. Run `npx tsc --noEmit` for type-level checks, then `npm run build` for Next.js page constraints. `tsc` alone can miss fatal buil
STEP|54|**Supabase is the data layer** ‚Äî `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` is server-only. Client uses `supabaseClient` from `@/lib/supabase-client`.
STEP|55|**Hermes agents are the AI layer** ‚Äî War Room specialists and analytics agents run as `hermes --profile yvon -s <agent-name> chat -q "..."` subprocesses.
STEP|56|**Never fabricate data** ‚Äî if a dashboard panel has no data, show an honest empty state. Never populate with hardcoded fake numbers. Seed data is acceptable only when clearly labeled as examples.
STEP|57|Use `child_process.spawn('hermes', [...])` from API route handlers
STEP|58|Pass `--profile yvon -s <agent-name>` to use the YVON profile with agent-specific skills
STEP|59|Set `HERMES_NO_COLOR: '1'` env var for clean output
STEP|60|Parse JSON from stdout with regex: `/\{[\s\S]*"key"[\s\S]*\}/`
STEP|61|Always provide a fallback when the agent can't spawn (server may lack Hermes)
STEP|62|Timeout: 90s for reads, 120s for full reports
STEP|63|Persist generated output to Supabase when appropriate
STEP|64|Define per-venture profiles in `_venture-context.ts` inside the screen folder
STEP|65|Each profile specifies: primary platform, KPI metrics, Kai focus area, accent color, empty state messaging
STEP|66|Use `getVentureProfile(slug)` to get the right profile at render time
STEP|67|Accent colors flow through to Kai's Read cards, buttons, and chart highlights
STEP|68|Different ventures have fundamentally different metrics (fashion: ER/ROAS/Reels; fintech: MRR/Churn/LTV:CAC)
STEP|69|Dashboard API aggregation pattern:** `references/dashboard-api-aggregation-pattern.md` ‚Äî real data dashboards with graceful degradation. Every data source gets an independent try/catch so one failure 
